izer to work simultaneously with built-in gesture recognizers by using "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/uikit\/uigesturerecognizerdelegate\/1624208-gesturerecognizer"},{"type":"text","text":", allowing you to enhance already existing gesture recognizers."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You can also add gesture recognizers that are only called when the default gesture recognizer fails (and vice versa), such as when a user taps on a part of the map that is not an annotation. The documentation for "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre\/MLNMapView","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" includes an example of how to create a fallback gesture recognizer."}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"If you would like to disable a specific set of gesture recognizers, such as zoom, you can set the Boolean value for the appropriate property to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"type":"text","text":". You can then add your own gesture recognizers to perform those actions."}]}],"kind":"content"}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"MapLibre"}],"title":"User Interactions","role":"article","roleHeading":"Article"},"sections":[],"abstract":[{"text":"Learn how to work with gesture recognizers","type":"text"}],"seeAlsoSections":[{"title":"Other Articles","identifiers":["doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Customizing_Fonts","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Info.plist_Keys","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/MultipleImagesExample","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Predicates_and_Expressions","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/Tile_URL_Templates","doc:\/\/org.swift.MyProject\/documentation\/MapLibre-Native-for-iOS\/For_Style_Authors"],"gener